        <mxCell id="XK4CYRICbNCdkGbWFszJ-6" parent="1" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Architects Daughter;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DArchitects%2BDaughter;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1A1A1A);" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;QUESTION:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is the application trying to achieve?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Assume that UI is rendered in the terminal (ui), the data is coming via kiteconnect or FlatTrade APIs (infrastructure).&amp;nbsp; Irrespective of how the UI is rendered or where the data comes from, the application will do what it is supposed to.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So what is it that the application is trying to achieve?" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="210" width="390" x="-80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="XK4CYRICbNCdkGbWFszJ-7" parent="1" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Architects Daughter;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DArchitects%2BDaughter;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#333333);align=left;spacing=14;" value="&lt;div&gt;ANSWER:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;- To display the underlying scrip as it ticks&lt;br&gt;- To display specific data from the option chain table&lt;br&gt;- To be able to see the difference between two periods.&lt;br&gt;- To select a visible range (so that users don&#39;t have too much data on their screen)&lt;br&gt;- To be able to upload the data on the database for replay&lt;br&gt;- A replay screen where user can replay the data stored on the database." vertex="1">
